abstract: The relative calm on Wall Street is worrying some investors. | A public finance crisis is developing in Puerto Rico. | A question mark hangs over Bill Gates at Microsoft. | One analyst has already set a high price target for Twitter’s stock.
snippet: The relative calm on Wall Street is worrying some investors. | A public finance crisis is developing in Puerto Rico. | A question mark hangs over Bill Gates at Microsoft. | One analyst has already set a high price target for Twitter’s stock.
lead_paragraph: Wall Street has predicted financial panic should the government default on its debt, but markets so far are showing few signs of fear, Nathaniel Popper reports in DealBook. “We all tell ourselves, ‘This is something that is not going to happen,’” said David Coard, the head of fixed-income trading at the Williams Capital Group.

headline.main: A Worrisome Calm on Wall Street
